Core Concepts of SpringBoot
  IoC Container (Inversion of Control)
    It is responsible for creating, managing, configuring application objects (called Beans)
    Using Dependency Injection  
      > Automatically injects dependencies into Beans
      > Manages Bean creation, initialization, destruction
      > Supports XML, annotation, and Java-based configuration
      
    There are two types of IoC containers in Spring
      1. Bean Factory
        The basic IoC container that provides fundamentals like Dependency Injection and management of Bean lifecycle

      2. Application Context
        Extends Bean Factory and provides additional features like event handling, internationalization, annotaion based-configuration


